<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 7:44PM CDT  by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Randolph, northeastern Fulton, northwestern Lawrence and northeastern
Sharp Counties through 815 PM CDT...
At 744 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mammoth Spring, moving southeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Highland in Sharp County...       Mammoth Spring...
Hardy...                          Ravenden...
Ravenden Springs...               Mammoth Spring State Park...
Williford...                      Armstrong...
Saddler Falls...                  Eleven Point...
Wirth...                          Ozark Acres...
Sitka...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
